[{'text': 'Hello Everyone,', 'start': 0.16, 'duration': 1.0}, {'text': 'After months of delays, here is the fourth
video in the dome greenhouse series. This', 'start': 1.16, 'duration': 3.15}, {'text': 'video doesn’t directly pertain to the actual
dome construction, but instead shows the site', 'start': 4.31, 'duration': 4.249}, {'text': 'preparation work. If you like chainsaws, tractors,
doodle bugs, and huge excavators, you’ll', 'start': 8.559, 'duration': 5.311}, {'text': 'love this segment!', 'start': 13.87, 'duration': 1.0}, {'text': 'The greenhouse is being constructed at the
edge of a field. About one and a half acres', 'start': 14.87, 'duration': 4.649}, {'text': 'needed to be timbered. Each tree needs to
be cut, delimbed, and removed from the area.', 'start': 19.519, 'duration': 4.882}, {'text': 'It’s a very time consuming process without
the aid of large logging equipment.', 'start': 24.401, 'duration': 4.298}, {'text': 'Having a tractor with forks helps to speed
up the clearing process. All the hardwood', 'start': 28.699, 'duration': 31.831}, {'text': 'logs and branches larger than a couple of
inches are collected and stacked in a large', 'start': 60.53, 'duration': 4.48}, {'text': 'pile. They will then be cut and split and
will be used to heat the greenhouse during', 'start': 65.01, 'duration': 4.29}, {'text': 'the winter. The larger pine logs will be sawn
into lumber.', 'start': 69.3, 'duration': 34.76}, {'text': 'All the smaller branches are collected and
placed in a large pile along the edge of the', 'start': 104.06, 'duration': 4.08}, {'text': 'field. This provides a habitat and shelter
area for various animals such as birds and', 'start': 108.14, 'duration': 5.1}, {'text': 'fox. In a few years, the branches will decompose.', 'start': 113.24, 'duration': 40.42}, {'text': 'My neighbor stopped by with his doodlebug
to help with some of the larger trees. A doodlebug', 'start': 153.66, 'duration': 9.16}, {'text': 'is a homemade piece of farming equipment that
is made from just about anything that can', 'start': 162.82, 'duration': 3.88}, {'text': 'be welded and bolted together.', 'start': 166.7, 'duration': 2.51}, {'text': 'This one is used as a logging skidder and
has large ag tires with chains, and a huge', 'start': 169.21, 'duration': 5.05}, {'text': 'winch for dragging logs. The winch is tied
into the transmission and has an awesome pulling', 'start': 174.26, 'duration': 5.42}, {'text': 'capacity. It has no problem dragging a few
complete trees at the same time. It also has', 'start': 179.68, 'duration': 6.56}, {'text': 'no problem driving over some of the toughest
terrain.', 'start': 186.24, 'duration': 2.61}, {'text': 'It’s time to bring in the big guns! The
area is filled with stumps intertwined with', 'start': 188.85, 'duration': 26.72}, {'text': 'large glacial boulders. They are no match
for this excavator which can easily slice', 'start': 215.57, 'duration': 4.44}, {'text': 'through the roots and throw around the boulders.', 'start': 220.01, 'duration': 2.42}, {'text': 'For the size of the machine, surprisingly,
it was able to do precision work by perfectly', 'start': 222.43, 'duration': 15.029}, {'text': 'leveling out the foundation hole in the footing
locations.', 'start': 237.459, 'duration': 19.06}, {'text': 'When they were done with the foundation hole,
we were left with large piles of rocks, topsoil,', 'start': 256.519, 'duration': 5.331}, {'text': 'stumps, and gravel. A nice round and level
hole is now ready for footings and foundation', 'start': 261.85, 'duration': 5.65}, {'text': 'wall. Mike Mulligan and his Steam Shovel couldn’t
have done a better job!', 'start': 267.5, 'duration': 6.46}, {'text': 'As always, thanks for watching, and please
subscribe for future videos!', 'start': 273.96, 'duration': 3.83}]
